[[Image:Curb gutter storm drain.JPG|thumb|right|Curb, gutter, and storm '''drain'''.]]

==English==

===Pronunciation===
*{{audio|en-us-drain.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-eɪn|-eɪn]]

===Noun===
'''drain'''
# A conduit allowing [[liquid]] to flow out of an otherwise contained volume.
#: ''The drain in the kitchen sink is clogged.''
# Something consuming resources and providing nothing in return.
#: ''That rental property is a drain on our finances.''
# (''vulgar'') An act of urination.

====Related terms====
*[[down the drain]]
*[[drainage]]
*[[drain the lizard]] (''vulgar'')

====Translations====
*CJKV Characters: [[渎]]
*Portuguese: [[drenagem]] {{f}} (1)
*Slovene: [[odtok]] ''m'' (1)

===Intransitive verb===
'''drain'''
# To cause [[liquid]] to [[flow]] out of.
#: ''Turn the pots upside down and let them drain.''

====Translations====
*Ukrainian: [[:uk:сохнути|со́хнути]]

===Transitive verb===
'''drain'''
# To cause liquid to flow out of.
#: ''Please drain the sink.  It's full of dirty water.''
# To convert a perennially wet place into a dry one.
#: ''They had to drain the swampy land before the parking lot could be built.''
# To deplete of energy or resources.
#: ''The stress of this job is really draining me.''

